# Codebase Map

Create or refresh the durable, repo-scoped codebase map that the discovery,
planning, and review skills consume.

## Invocation
```bash
slipway codebase-map --json
```

## Contract
- Scaffolds the canonical map directory and the fixed brownfield document set, and
  reports `codebase_map_dir`, `codebase_map_docs`, `status`, and `doc_states`.
- Use this during standalone discovery (when `slipway next` would return
  `no_active_change`). Inside an active change, the `slipway-codebase-mapping`
  skill may instead read `input_context.codebase_map_*` from `slipway next --json`.
- This command only creates/refreshes the structure; authoring durable content
  into the scaffolded docs is the host AI's job.

## Flags
- `--json`: JSON output
